tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows mildly elevated creatinine, chloride, total cholesterol, and LDL cholesterol, suggesting possible early renal impairment and increased cardiovascular risk. HbA1c and glucose are within target ranges, indicating good glycemic control. Other electrolytes and lipid parameters are within normal limits. Recommend further evaluation of renal function and lipid management.
